# Code Validation Defaults

After code implementation, default to the smallest validation that directly exercises the changed behavior.

- Run focused tests for the code you changed when a suitable test command exists.
- Prefer file-scoped or package-scoped test commands over full project suites.
- Use targeted lint/typecheck only when it is the established code test for the touched area or needed to verify the change.
- Do not automatically run dev servers, production builds, full test suites, broad repo checks, `git diff`, `git status`, `git version`, or dependency commands after normal implementation.
- Run the full validation suite only when the developer explicitly asks for a full suite, build, dev run, release check, commit/PR preparation, or similar broad verification.
- If no focused code test is available, say so briefly and report the validation you skipped.
